    <main id="main">
      <div id="img-div">
        <h1 id="title">Mowtown's Bassist</h1>
        <img id="image" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/3/3f/James_Jamerson.jpeg">
        <figcaption id="img-caption"> James Jamerson playing with the Earl Van Dyke Band at Blues Unlimited in Detroit, 1964</figcaption>
      </div>
      <div id="tribute-info">
        <label for="bio">Biography: </label>
        <ul id="bio">
          <li>Born 1936 in South Carolina</li>
          <li>Moved to Detroit in high school and started learning upright bass</li>
          <li>Offered and declined a music school scholarship and played in Detroit jazz clubs instead</li>
          <li>Started working regularly with Berry Gordy at Hitsville USA, the home of the Motown label</li>
          <li>Moved to L.A. and stopped working with Motown in the 70s</li>
          <li>Died of cirrhosis due to lifelong alcoholism in 1983</li>
        </ul>
        <label for="playing-style">Playing Style: </label>
        <ul id="playing-style">
          <li>Mostly played with only index finger</li>
          <li>Used a pickguard</li>
          <li>Expanded complexity of bass lines to more closely resemble jazz bass playing, with more chromatic lines and non-chord tones</li>
          <li>Tight connection with drummer</li>
          <li>Syncopated lines</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <footer>
        <p>For more info, read <a id="tribute-link" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/James_Jamerson" target="_blank">this</a>
